items.name: 90s VHS TV Show Style - LoCon
items.description:
It is one of my first models that I trained thanks to this guide:

[Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

There are LoRas and Checkpoints that reference the VHS style, and after this inspiration, I came up with the idea of being able to create a LoCon of a VHS stylized taking references to interviews, television programs, movies and commercials from the late 80s and mid 90s to create an effect not so destroyed or glitched by the quality of the VHS of that time. It was intended for portraits more than for other purposes, for landscapes and others, I am not 100% sure that it works well.

It was trained by approximately 140 portrait-type photos extracted from video fragments and other image sources.

In the training I used this checkpoint with SD 1.5 as a base, so I also recommend that you use this checkpoint in conjunction with the LoCon to obtain the most faithful result to the one I had.

(Surely there will be better combinations, better options, but that I have not tested or documented.)

How to install LoCon:

  • How to use models · civitai/civitai Wiki (github.com)

How to use it:

Prompts: 90VHS, vhs still from tv, + whatever-you-want

I also recommend using epiNoiseoffset_v1.

Negative Prompts: rz-neg-foranalogportrait, cartoon, 3d, ((disfigured)), ((bad art)), ((deformed)), ((poorly drawn)), ((extra limbs)), ((close up)), ((b&w)), weird colors, blurry

You can experiment with negative prompts, but for me ‘rz-neg-foranalogportrait’ give very good results.

I recommend these parameters:

  • LoCon Strength: 1.0

  • Size: 512 x 512 - Truly I have not tried with other resolutions, I think the most stable is this measure.

  • Sampling Steps: between 20 and 40 is the most stable.

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ SDE Karras works very well for portraits.

Using this LoCon in img2img interesting results are achieved maintaining 512x512, and with these settings:

Same settings as txt2img but with these differences:

  • CFG Scale: 26 ~

  • Denoising strength: 0,5 - sometimes 0,8

I invite you to experiment with checkpoints, mix them with other Loras and share them!

Don’t forget to put the prompts you used, thank you!

items.name: djz Never Late
items.description:
Demo images use Danger Zoo ~ Johnsons Negative TI Collection ~
Lora version: djzNeverLate

These "strong style" Models are intended to be merged with each other and any model for Stable Diffusion 2.1

I recommend merging with 0.5 (50/50 blend) then using prompt weighting to control the Aesthetic gradient.

example merged model prompt with automatic1111:

(neverlate:1) (othermodeltoken:1)

if you drop the "djz" and the "V21" what remains is the token you need to call up the concept in the model. All examples shown were the Raw Token, no other words. Tokens are case sensitive and in almost all models it will match the filename.

It is possible to merge these models with each other using a different value. It is possible to pair models and then merge those resulting models. In this way we can blend abstract concepts together and then weight the tokens to achieve the result we may wish to create. Of course to eliminate all those tokens, you can simply train a new custom model from the outputs, which means you are back to a single token.

items.name: t800
items.description:
Trained with about 240 images on stock SD 1.5. I get the best results from about 0.8 weight. Always use the t800 tag and add more tags onto it. Add the 'cyborg' tag for terminators that still look like humans. Add the 'robot' and 'endoskeleton' tags for terminators that just look like metal robot skeletons. Add 'wounded' or 'heavily wounded' to show more battle damage on the cyborgs.

There are some non-arnold terminators in the training data but not many, so most of your cyborgs will skew towards looking like ol' arnie. I haven't had a ton of luck with inpainting, but txt2img and img2img seem to work fairly well.

For the training data, I edited, cropped, and resized each one by hand because most of the automated stuff was doing a terrible job of focusing on the right spot. txt2image will still sometimes spit out endoskeletons with the head cropped out of view though. I also manually added tags to each image because all of the automated AIs are astonishingly bad at tagging t800s. There are slightly more robot endoskeleton images in the training data than cyborg images, but I tried to keep it somewhat balanced.

This is the first model I've uploaded. If you like it, let me know. If you don't, constructive feedback helps. I spent a ton of time on this, so If you merge it into something else please include a mention about my contribution to the effort.

Example prompt: john doe as a heavily damaged t800 cyborg

Go light on the negative prompts. Note that a lot of common negative prompts might directly contradict this model. Negative prompts like "ugly" or "scarred" may completely negate the damaged look normally seen on a t800.

items.name: Calm Art Concept
items.description:
My first embedding and attempt at recreating the nsfw artists "Calm" art. Trained with 40 images.

Using prompts like 1girl, 1boy, pointy ears, elf, colored skin usually gives the best results. For now its more or less "hit or miss". I intend on improving the embedding further. You will notice that you mostly get elf girls, which most of the training pictures consisted of.

There really is no exact trigger word, just using the embedding works for me at least. I have tested the embedding on anyhentai, MeinaHentai, revAnimated, Cetusmix, AOM3, and on everyone i got some pretty good results. So i can safely say that it works on most models.

Alot of the images i used for training contained watermarks, so you should add on the negative prompt: watermark, signature, patreon username, patreon logo,

Example images were created with very simple prompts. Some of them i used inpainting on to remove the logos and watermarks. Some i fixed the faces on. Did very little inpainting tho.

Settings that worked best for me:

Sampling Method: Euler A

Sampling steps: 20-25

CFG Scale: 6-8

Hires.fix: upscale by: 1.5x -- Hires steps: 10 -- Denoising strength: 0.3

Would love to get some feedback and see your creations :D

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description:
This is almost a complete change from the first version. I re-did the whole training and this version 2 gives much crispier images.

The main difference between the two versions is that v1 gives much more consistent images of the elves but the quality is usually very blurry. The v2 on the other hand gives much less images of elves but the quality is much better. In other words, you have to use tags like elf, elf girl, pointy ears etc.. to get the same "results" as v1.

Another thing is that v2 gives alot of results with nature/water falls/monsters in the background because the training images had these. You need to write your prompts while keeping this in mind.

Once again, there is no Trigger words, just using the embedding will give results.

items.name: Sangheili - Halo
items.description:
Wort, wort, wort... It's the Sangheili, from Halo!

This is a lora trained on a whopping 291 hand picked images of the Sangheili alien race from the Halo series! It was trained on mostly digital art, with a little 3d content in there, too. It wasn't trained on any specific character, but just the race in general. I'm quite satisfied with the results of this lora, mostly because there are so many different... depictions of sangheilis online, and this model captures most of them. It was trained on e621-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most .ckpts, however, since it was trained on e621-style tags, it might be ideal to use a model that is trained on a furry art. I would recommend using the Lawlas's Mix. It gave me great results and I used it for most of the example images.

NOTES:

-It can also do their armor pretty well. You can change the color of the armor pretty easily, too.

-Their weird little mouth appendages are a bit inconsistent, and they have a hard time expressing themselves because of it, but if you emphasize certain emotion tags enough it'll work

-It was trained on a fair amount of male sangheilis too, so it can do those just as well as female ones.

-It somehow gets the weird toe and finger alien anatomy pretty well.

Also, see my Halo Spartan Lora: https://civitai.com/models/21287/spartans-halo

Example prompt: (See example images, all images should still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)

Waaaaaahhhhhh!!!

She's easily the most finnicky of the bunch. She'll probably require inpainting no matter what you do. The prompt azuki uniform should get her outfit right when paired with the white apron prompt, and you can try the striped tail prompt if you like.

Good luck, share the stuff you make here! I'd love to see it.

items.name: bartolomeobari Style LoRa
items.description:
This is my first model trained for LoRa. It turned out pretty good (especially highres), considering the time spent on making the dataset.

I recommend using 0.6-0.8 for weights, although 1 still looks decent. No trigger words are required, however you can also include bartolomeobari in your prompt. Trained on HeavenOrangeMix, but other anime models should also work. It plays well with other LoRas, but weights need to be lowered otherwise the image gets fried.

Notes

The model tends to produce close-ups, so I recommend adding close-up to negatives. Additionally, the default face expression isn't neutral and tends towards tokens like :3 or wavy mouth. Adding face expressions to your prompts or adding the above to your negative prompt should improve your generations. After I get some time to clean up the dataset and retrain the model, these problems should go away.

items.name: SDArt : Elemental Flowers
items.description:
Model presentation

This is a model related to the "Picture of the Week" contest on Stable Diffusion discord.

You can find this dataset in a more complete model, SDArt : Complete Edition.

This current "classic version" responds to tokens for the 4 elements.

This current "user token version" is trained on dedicated tokens per user, and doesn't work like you may be used to.

I try to make a model out of all the submissions, for people to continue enjoy the theme after the event, and see a little of their designs in other people's creations. The token stays "SDArt" and I balance the learning on the low side, so that it doesn't just replicate creations.

The pictures were tagged using the token "SDArt", and an arbitrary token given to the user that submitted it.

The dataset is available below and is composed of 49 pictures.


This week's theme

ˑ༄ؘ ۪۫۫ ▹▫◃ ۪۫۫ ༄ؘ ˑ

Emerald leaves, crimson petals, and a fragrance so sweet – Nature's art, a canvas so neat. is it the fiery passion of a red rose, or the tranquil bliss of a bluebell that grows?

Love is like a garden of these elemental treasures, each with its own charm, each with its own measures.

ˑ༄ؘ ۪۫۫ ▹▫◃ ۪۫۫ ༄ؘ ˑ

  • Create images of flowers representing the four elements: fire, water, earth, and air.

  • Use colors and shapes that capture the essence of one or each element, and consider the symbolism and associations associated with them to create unique designs.

  • Consider the symbolism and associations of each element as you create your images. What emotions or concepts do they evoke, and how can you incorporate that into your designs?

  • What will your elemental flower bloom into? Where does it grow? What is it surrounded by? Even better-- what's your flower called? Name it! Today's example flowers were made by me ^^ enjoy!

ˑ༄ؘ ۪۫۫ ▹▫◃ ۪۫۫ ༄ؘ ˑ

Tested on Windows 10+ and Nvidia GPU-based cards

items.name: Volleyball Uniform | LyCORIS and LoRA
items.description:
If you create any good images using this LoRA, please consider sharing them by leaving a review. Thank you!

2.0 update

This model has been changed to LyCORIS.

For people who do not use LyCORIS, I still provide a 2.0 version of LoRA, which has a different performance.

  • This version includes real beach volleyball athletes, Sports_bikini to trigger.

  • The beach volleyball court settings are Outdoors, Beach and Volleyball_net, accessories include Sunglasses, Eyewear_on_head, Cap (or visor cap)

  • For indoor volleyball players, Volleyball_uniform, Indoor_stadium to trigger, accessories include elbow pad, knee pads

  • The training data has changed a lot, so there may be a significant difference compared to the old version.

1.0

  • This LoRA is mainly trained on Asian volleyball athletes and may not be suitable for generating beach volleyball images.

  • Volleyball uniform and Indoor stadium to trigger

  • If unwanted volleyball objects keep appearing, try using Sportswear instead of volleyball uniform.

  • Basketball objects or actions may sometimes appear and affects the image. Consider putting them in the negative prompts.

  • In some checkpoints, using "realistic" can make girls look TALLER (which is important).

  • Sometimes it may be difficult to generate multiple girls, you can try using "group selfie", "girl sandwich", or "looking at another".

  • The volleyball actions are still difficult to generate. You can try using "jumping" or "spiking".

items.name: Thunderbolt-ElectricShock 十万伏特触电
items.description:
Originally, I intended to create a Thunderbolt electric shock lora, but unexpectedly, I discovered that it can also be used as a bone king lora (laughs).

Usage:

1. For an electric shock character, use keywords such as electric shock, no humans, skeleton, bone, skull, and use an anime model with weights ranging from 0.5-1.

2. When used with a character lora, keep the keywords the same, and use weights ranging from 0.8-1.1.

Remember not to add high-quality prefixes (such as masterpiece, ultra-detailed) or negative words (such as worst quality, low quality, EasyNegative).

If you use Hires. Fix, Denoising needs to be adjusted to around 0.2-0.3. Use XYZ to choose the style you like.

3. Inpainting can also be used with weights ranging from 0.7-1 and a Denoising value of 0.50-0.60 (this value is subtle and may need to be adjusted to 0.01 for different images). Depending on the situation, increase the weight of electric shock or bone, skull.

4.Remove the electric shock to become a bone king lora :P.

原本是想做一个十万伏特的触电lora，意外地发现也可以当作骨王lora（笑）。

用法：

1.使用electricshock, no humans, skeleton,bone, skull,产生触电的角色，使用动漫模型，权重0.5-1都行。

2.结合人物lora使用，关键词不变，权重0.8-1.1。

记得不要加高质量前缀（例如masterpiece,ultra-detailed）及负面词（例如worst quality, low quality,EasyNegative)。

如果你使用Hires. Fix的话，Denoising需要调低，大概0.2-0.3。推荐使用XYZ选出你喜欢的幅度。

3.inpainting也可以使用，权重0.7-1，Denoising为0.50-0.60（这个值很微妙，有时候需要精确到0.01，对于不同的图需要多试几次）。视情况增加electricshock,或者bone, skull的权重。

4.去掉electricshock变成骨王lora（大雾）。
